Every day we have to make a choice.⁣
⁣
You can use your past...⁣
⁣
the memories of those we lost⁣
the love we once felt⁣
the heartbreak⁣
the challenges⁣
the neglect⁣
the injustice⁣
and the pain⁣
⁣
to hold you back.  To 𝙡𝙞𝙢𝙞𝙩 your thoughts and paralyze you from moving forward.⁣

you can use it to 𝙢𝙤𝙩𝙞𝙫𝙖𝙩𝙚 you to become the person you know you need to become based on the lessons life has given to you.⁣
⁣
Every day YOU get to choose how you react.⁣
⁣
Does life happen to you...for you...with you...or does life just happen?⁣
⁣
Depending on how you answer will tell me a lot about your 𝘦𝘮𝘰𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯𝘢𝘭 𝘪𝘯𝘵𝘦𝘭𝘭𝘪𝘨𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘦!⁣
⁣
You see…all of my successful friends…ALL OF THEM…choose to be optimistic.  They choose to be positive (𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘯 𝘸𝘩𝘦𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘪𝘳 𝘣𝘢𝘤𝘬𝘴 𝘢𝘨𝘢𝘪𝘯𝘴𝘵 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘸𝘢𝘭𝘭). They choose to use their pain as motivation to dominate their goals & create a better future for themselves & their families.⁣
⁣
It’s a choice.  Actually…it’s an OBLIGATION.⁣
⁣
They believe it’s their duty to take 𝗲𝘅𝘁𝗿𝗲𝗺𝗲 𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 & learn from their mistakes.⁣
⁣
No excuses.⁣
No blaming others.⁣
No being a victim.⁣
⁣
Just them accepting their situation & their environment as life happening for them & converting that energy into motivation to power forward.⁣
⁣
Today is a new day!⁣
⁣
𝗛𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗼𝘀𝗲 𝘁𝗼 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆?⁣
⁣
For those who took the time to read this...this message was meant for you 😘⁣
⁣
You're welcome,⁣
⁣
C.S.⁣
⁣

𝙄𝙩'𝙨 𝙛𝙪𝙣𝙣𝙮 𝙝𝙤𝙬 𝙩𝙝𝙞𝙣𝙜𝙨 𝙬𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙤𝙪𝙩…⁣
⁣
I remember asking for help...so desperate for a path...yet they all ignored me.⁣
⁣
I remember them pushing back and telling me every reason it won't work out when I told them my plans.⁣
⁣
I remember their bad advice and misguided opinions even when I didn't ask for it.⁣
⁣
I remember the mean underhanded comments they left on my facebook posts.⁣
⁣
I remember being so alone working on my goals day and night.⁣
⁣
I remember the awkwardness I felt going to all those meetings and events trying to build relationships.⁣
⁣
I remember the silence of the phone when people hung up on me.⁣
⁣
I remember the 1000's of "NO'S" I got before I got good enough to earn a "YES".⁣
⁣
I remember being passed over, pushed around, and sidelined by every major player in my local market when I tried to do business with them.⁣
⁣
I also remember the feeling I had when I was cashing my first $40,000 #realestateinvesting profit check…⁣
⁣
then going on to do over 2000 deals…⁣
⁣
becoming a millionaire by 28 & a multi-millionaire by age 30.⁣
⁣
I also remember the feeling I had when I retired my parents and told them that they would never have to stress about #money ever again.⁣
⁣
I also remember watching all their faces the day I pulled up in my brand new all black Mansory Rolls Royce on 24in Forgiato’s.⁣
⁣
& the Lambos & Porsche 911 GT3RS really fucked them up 😈⁣
⁣
I also remember how rewarding it was to build multiple companies and hire over 100 amazing team members.⁣
⁣
I also remember the look on my wifes face when I bought our first mansion and handed her the keys.⁣
⁣
Now I do whatever the fuck I want.⁣
⁣
total⁣
fucking⁣
control 😎⁣
⁣
Many of the same people that hated either asked me for a loan...or a job...or I dominated them and put their asses out of business.⁣
⁣
Yeah...it's funny how things work out...𝗪𝗛𝗘𝗡 𝗬𝗢𝗨 𝗣𝗨𝗧 𝗜𝗡 𝗧𝗛𝗘 𝗪𝗢𝗥𝗞 𝗔𝗡𝗗 𝗕𝗘𝗟𝗜𝗘𝗩𝗘 𝗜𝗡 𝗬𝗢𝗨𝗥𝗦𝗘𝗟𝗙.⁣
⁣
